.ad b
.SH DESCRIPTION
Each of these functions has tha same ol' dirty behavior as its counterpart
without tha "_unlocked" suffix, except dat they do not use locking
(they do not set locks theyselves, n' do not test fo' tha presence
of locks set by others) n' hence is thread-unsafe.
See
.BR flockfile (3).
.SH CONFORMING TO
Da four functions
.BR getc_unlocked (),
.BR getchar_unlocked (),
.BR putc_unlocked (),
.BR putchar_unlocked ()
are up in POSIX.1-2001.

Da nonstandard
.BR *_unlocked ()
variants occur on all dem UNIX systems, n' is available up in recent glibc.
.\" E.g., up in HP-UX 10.0. In HP-UX 10.30 they is called obsolescent, and
.\" moved ta a cold-ass lil compatibilitizzle library.
.\" Available up in HP-UX 10.0: clearerr_unlocked, fclose_unlocked,
.\" feof_unlocked, ferror_unlocked, fflush_unlocked, fgets_unlocked,
.\" fgetwc_unlocked, fgetws_unlocked, fileno_unlocked, fputs_unlocked,
.\" fputwc_unlocked, fputws_unlocked, fread_unlocked, fseek_unlocked,
.\" ftell_unlocked, fwrite_unlocked, getc_unlocked, getchar_unlocked,
.\" getw_unlocked, getwc_unlocked, getwchar_unlocked, putc_unlocked,
.\" putchar_unlocked, puts_unlocked, putws_unlocked, putw_unlocked,
.\" putwc_unlocked, putwchar_unlocked, rewind_unlocked, setvbuf_unlocked,
.\" ungetc_unlocked, ungetwc_unlocked.
They should probably not be used.
